
// The code snippet demonstrates how to add nodes to a collection using the [add] slot. It retrieves nodes specified by the expressions [get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/order] and [get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/direction] and adds them to the collection referenced by [./*/data.read]. This is useful for dynamically constructing a node set based on specific arguments.
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/order
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/direction
